{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-quick-poll-of-data-science-research-oriented-professionals-fd2fd0629d7", "time": 1683016106.37477, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/a-quick-poll-of-data-science-research-oriented-professionals-fd2fd0629d7/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "A Quick Poll of Data Science & Research Oriented Professionals, Methods & Results | by Adam Ross Nelson | Towards Data Science", "h1": "A Quick Poll of Data Science & Research Oriented Professionals, Methods & Results", "description": "While speaking with current, former, and aspiring data scientists I hear a common complaint. Recruiters will screen you based on your salary history or your salary expectations. I\u2019m troubled when\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://twitter.com/adamrossnelson", "anchor_text": "@adamrossnelson", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/arnelson/", "anchor_text": "Adam Ross Nelson", "paragraph_index": 13}], "all_paragraphs": ["While speaking with current, former, and aspiring data scientists I hear a common complaint. Recruiters will screen you based on your salary history or your salary expectations.", "I\u2019m troubled when recruiters do this, not only for the candidate\u2019s sake, but also for the recruiter\u2019s sake. To drive the conversation a bit further, I conducted a poll using social media.", "I ran this poll in late October and early November of 2020. I posted the poll on LinkedIn, Twitter, and Facebook. I used hashtags, keywords, and forums that I thought would encourage responses from those that work in data science or other research oriented professions. I also promoted the poll (via Twitter) to boost response numbers.", "The prompts and posts that accompanied the polls asked respondents to think about their current or most recent job search when deciding how to respond.", "These polls collected 343 responses. There were 269 from Twitter, 47 from Facebook, and 27 from LinkedIn. The visual here aggregates the responses from all three platforms.", "The subsequent visual below provides a view of disaggregated results.", "While, the combined results show that a majority of respondents indicated salary as a second, third, fourth, or lower concern the response patterns across platforms were different. Among the Facebook responses, a majority did indicate salary was the first concern. Among Twitter and LinkedIn responses salary was not the first concern.", "This and the subsequent visual collapse responses from four categories to two.", "This brief, not-scientific poll, indicates that data scientists and other research professionals consider salary to be an important factor in their job search. But perhaps among half of all available candidates have other considerations they would consider more important.", "Despite the many known and unknown weaknesses of this poll, it brings light to the discussion related to asking about salary during the job recruitment process.", "When recruiters ask this question I have a concern for candidates. Candidates are seemingly faced with the impossible choice of suggesting a salary they think the recruiter will meet (potentially being under-compensated) or suggesting a salary that represents a deserved and earned career advancement (potentially risking rejection).", "I also have a concern for recruiters. When recruiters screen candidates early in the discussion on salary requirements the opportunity to learn from candidates what really matters is lost. This strategy also risks missing out on quality candidates who can be recruited and attracted to work for factors not related to salary. Related, candidates who respond to non-salary factors now may be resistant to subsequent attempts to be later recruited away by other organizations.", "A better approach would be for recruiters to ask candidates \u201cwhat are among your most important considerations in the job offer negotiation?\u201d Then, listen to the candidate. After that, speak to the considerations that matter to the candidate. And then during and after onboarding be sure to further address the wants and desires you now know to be important to your new employee.", "Thanks for reading. Send me your thoughts and ideas. You can write just to say hey. And if you really need to tell me how I got it wrong I look forward to chatting soon. Twitter: @adamrossnelson LinkedIn: Adam Ross Nelson.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Ask about my free career course. I mentor new (\ud83d\udcab) and aspiring data scientists enter (\ud83d\udeaa) and level up (\ud83d\udcc8) in the field."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ffd2fd0629d7&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-quick-poll-of-data-science-research-oriented-professionals-fd2fd0629d7&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-quick-poll-of-data-science-research-oriented-professionals-fd2fd0629d7&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/sign